<subSubSection id="D7DA68FEFFE3E87AFFB7E4E8FE40A710" pageId="19" pageNumber="422" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="9F7F3B75FFE3E87AFFB7E4E8FE40A710" blockId="19.[113,1089,761,881]" pageId="19" pageNumber="422">
<emphasis id="ADB4E767FFE3E87AFFB7E4E8FEEAA770" bold="true" box="[113,260,761,785]" pageId="19" pageNumber="422">Distribution.</emphasis>
A species occuring in India (e. g. 
<bibRefCitation id="FB514684FFE3E87AFDB2E4E8FCE8A770" author="MAULIK S." box="[628,774,761,785]" pageId="19" pageNumber="422" refId="ref13919" refString="MAULIK S. 1936: The fauna of British India including Ceylon and Burma. Coleoptera, Chrysomelidae (Galerucinae). Taylor and Francis, London, xv + 648 pp." type="book" year="1936">MAULIK 1936</bibRefCitation>
), Nepal (
<bibRefCitation id="FB514684FFE3E87AFCA1E4E8FBE0A770" author="TAKIZAWA H." box="[871,1038,761,785]" pageId="19" pageNumber="422" pagination="275 - 291" refId="ref14247" refString="TAKIZAWA H. 1990: Chrysomelid beetles of Nepal, Northeastern India and Western Sikkim collected by the Himalaya expeditions of the National Science Museum, Tokyo (Part 2). Japanese Journal of Entomology 58: 275 - 291." type="journal article" year="1990">TAKIZAWA 1990</bibRefCitation>
), Sri Lanka (
<bibRefCitation id="FB514684FFE3E87AFF00E508FE4FA750" author="MOHAMEDSAID M. S." box="[198,417,793,817]" pageId="19" pageNumber="422" pagination="1 - 7" refId="ref14001" refString="MOHAMEDSAID M. S. 1997: The galerucine beetles of Sri Lanka, with descriptions of two new species (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae). Stobaeana 9: 1 - 7." type="journal article" year="1997">MOHAMEDSAID 1997</bibRefCitation>
), and continetal Yemen (present paper). Recorded also from Sudan (
<bibRefCitation id="FB514684FFE3E87AFF02E528FE6EA730" author="LABOISSIERE V." box="[196,384,825,849]" pageId="19" pageNumber="422" pagination="190 - 193" refId="ref13843" refString="LABOISSIERE V. 1926: Description d'un nouveau genre et de trois nouvelles especes de Galerucini africains (Col.). Bulletin de la Societe Entomologique de France 1926: 190 - 193." type="journal article" year="1926">LABOISSIÈRE 1926</bibRefCitation>
) under the name 
<taxonomicName id="58C040F6FFE3E87AFDF8E52BFC11A730" authority="Laboissiere, 1926" authorityName="Laboissiere" authorityYear="1926" box="[574,1023,825,849]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Neorudolphia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="19" pageNumber="422" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bedfordi">
<emphasis id="ADB4E767FFE3E87AFDF8E52BFCDAA730" box="[574,820,826,849]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="422">Neorudolphia bedfordi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="FB514684FFE3E87AFCFAE528FC11A730" author="LABOISSIERE V." box="[828,1023,825,849]" pageId="19" pageNumber="422" pagination="190 - 193" refId="ref13843" refString="LABOISSIERE V. 1926: Description d'un nouveau genre et de trois nouvelles especes de Galerucini africains (Col.). Bulletin de la Societe Entomologique de France 1926: 190 - 193." type="journal article" year="1926">Laboissière, 1926</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<emphasis id="ADB4E767FFE3E87AFBCCE528FE40A710" bold="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="422">
First record from 
<collectingCountry id="E7D77BE5FFE3E87AFEC7E548FE47A710" box="[257,425,857,881]" name="Socotra Island" pageId="19" pageNumber="422">Socotra Island</collectingCountry>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
